  # Best ranking: Wilson score lower bound (95% confidence interval on upvote ratio).
  # Rewards posts that are both reliably upvoted AND have enough votes to be statistically significant.
  #
  # BestEvents (posts 01-10): upvote% 83–92%, 100 voters each
  #   → Wilson scores ≈ 0.745 (post-01, 83%) to 0.850 (post-10, 92%) → WIN
  # TopEvents (posts 41-50): upvote% 61–70%, 500 voters each
  #   → Wilson scores ≈ 0.567 (post-41, 61%) to 0.658 (post-50, 70%) → lose
  #
  # Why TopEvents lose despite more voters: Wilson score is asymptotically bounded by the
  # upvote ratio — Wilson(70%) → 0.70 as n→∞, so 70% can never reach the BestEvents
  # minimum of 0.745 (83% upvote ratio). More voters narrow the interval but can't raise
  # the ceiling above the true proportion.
  #
  # Wilson score ordering within BestEvents is strictly by upvote%:
  #   post-10 (92%): 0.850 > post-09 (91%): 0.838 > ... > post-01 (83%): 0.745
  # karma per post: postId 01→66, 02→68, ..., 10→84  (upvote% = 83 + (postId−1))
